1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:38,246
Are you sure about the complications
you're getting into?

2
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:40,665
Do you know what gives me courage?

3
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:42,625
-What?
-You.

4
00:00:51,926 --> 00:00:56,347
I believe you now have eyes and ears
inside their organization.

5
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,484
You just have to believe in yourself.

6
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:00,537
I was practicing my… judo roll.

7
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,381
I told you.

8
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,677
Yes.

9
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:17,929
Doesn’t it feel a bit too much?

10
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:21,391
Do I really have to ride a private jet?

11
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,226
It’s scary.

12
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:28,773
Yes, sweetheart. And trust me,

13
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:30,692
it really suits you.

14
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:33,903
You actually look cute.

15
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:49,961
Dad,

16
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:51,880
can you slow down a bit?

17
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:59,012
Do you want me to introduce him
to the office already?

18
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:00,054
Dad.

19
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,974
Give us a couple of days first
to settle down. Okay?

20
00:03:03,057 --> 00:03:05,268
And Mikoy still has some things to fix.

21
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,313
All right. Take your time.

22
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,243
‎All right.

23
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,505
Kian briefly woke up earlier.

24
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,426
The next time he wakes up,

25
00:03:38,509 --> 00:03:40,261
please call me
and Agent Sianong immediately.

26
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:42,222
Because we need to talk to him right away.

27
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:49,687
-All right.
-Okay.

28
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:59,572
Bok, why did you talk
to the mom like that?

29
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,074
Did I say anything wrong?

30
00:04:01,157 --> 00:04:03,201
"The next time he wakes up,

31
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,911
please call me and Agent Sianong

32
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,579
because we want
to talk to him right away."

33
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:17,382
Yes, I’m interested

34
00:04:17,465 --> 00:04:19,717
in the new information
that Agent Kian can give.

35
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:23,638
But that doesn't mean
I don't care about his situation.

36
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,725
The most important thing right now
is that our teammate recovers,

37
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:31,980
and there is no new information
more important than his life.

38
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:33,398
That's my point.

39
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:34,607
Actually…

40
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:36,109
-Kian…
-Kian.

41
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,616
Mikoy is in danger.

42
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,119
Someone wants to kill him.

43
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:52,041
Jepoy.

44
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:55,461
I'm sorry,

45
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:58,589
I wasn't there when you needed me.

46
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,726
Who the hell did this to you?

47
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:19,736
PHILIPPINE UNIVERSITY

48
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:37,211
Bro?

49
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:41,549
Bro?

50
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,553
Bro, is that really you?

51
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,265
-How are you?
-Nice outfit.

52
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:51,309
When did you get back?

53
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:52,477
Just suddenly,

54
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,813
and I told Mom and Dad
not to tell you yet,

55
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:57,106
because I wanted to surprise you.

56
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,983
So… Surprise!

57
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,902
I am suprised!

58
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:03,571
But now I know why
those two went radio silent on me.

59
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:05,990
They ignored me for days.

60
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:10,453
Turns out you were hiding
a surprise from me.

61
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,414
So, you came from home?

62
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,707
Yes.

63
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,084
Everything's actually good there.

64
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:18,836
Did you know there's
a new oven in Dad’s bakery?

65
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,921
It’s nice.

66
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:21,339
You know what, bro?

67
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:23,883
They really saved up the money
you’ve been sending.

68
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:27,386
Actually, they even want
to open a branch in the mall.

69
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,472
Huh? Nice.

70
00:06:29,972 --> 00:06:31,724
They didn’t tell me anything.

71
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,309
Okay.

72
00:06:33,392 --> 00:06:35,019
But…

73
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,648
What is it?

74
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,275
Why do you look like that?

75
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:42,318
How do I look?

76
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:46,739
You look like a big shot now.

77
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:51,661
-Did you marry a foreigner or something?
-Whoa!

78
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:53,579
You're crazy! What foreigner?

79
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,124
Not a foreigner.

80
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:57,959
But me.

81
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:05,133
Your brother Mikoy's girlfriend.

82
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:10,263
Hey, hey, hey. Easy.

83
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:11,639
That's my girlfriend.

84
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:20,815
Just keep calling. We need to warn him.

85
00:07:20,898 --> 00:07:22,692
The subscriber cannot be reached.

86
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:25,570
Mikoy, please answer your phone.

87
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,076
Really?

88
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,745
Just one drinking session
and bro already got you?

89
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:37,874
Tell me about it.

90
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:41,294
He even said that he is
the nation’s top drinker.

91
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:43,254
What he meant was a "player".

92
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:46,215
-Huh?
-He got me with drinks first.

93
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,675
Then, when I got tipsy,

94
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:49,760
he suddenly made his move.

95
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:51,304
Whoa!

96
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:53,264
And me being soft-hearted…

97
00:07:53,347 --> 00:07:56,267
Cut to I’m here, in Manila.

98
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:59,437
Living like a Disney princess,
"Part of your world."

99
00:08:00,688 --> 00:08:02,106
You, bro!

100
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,774
You’re really something.

101
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:05,026
-You’re my idol.
-Whatever.

102
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,278
Hey, don’t believe her.

103
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:08,654
The truth is,

104
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,865
she’s the one who went after me.

105
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:12,992
-What?
-Yes, right.

106
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,160
Oh please.

107
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:16,621
What are you? A historical revisionist?

108
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,873
That’s bad! Don’t rewrite the story.

109
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,500
Okay, okay.

110
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,543
Fine, fine, it’s me.

111
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:25,171
But here’s the real good news, Angelito.

112
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,965
Chiara’s family has a company here,

113
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,717
and officially,

114
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:34,514
her dad wants me
to help run their company.

115
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:36,140
Wow!

116
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,809
That’s great, bro!

117
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:39,852
Sis, did you know?

118
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:42,021
It doesn’t show,

119
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:46,317
but he finished a business course
with high honors!

120
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:51,447
But you know, if only our bakery
hadn’t been pawned and gone bankrupt,

121
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,950
he would’ve studied here in Manila too.

122
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,202
But no,

123
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:59,539
he had to help Mom and Dad.

124
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:02,250
So he got stuck in our small bakery.

125
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,460
And because of me,

126
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,922
that’s why he went abroad,
so I could study in Manila.

127
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,466
But then…

128
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,637
all I gave back was shame.

129
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,472
What are you talking about?

130
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,521
I think I’ll leave you two.

131
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:27,233
You probably need to talk.

132
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:30,528
I’ll just be around
or wait at the parking area.

133
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:32,780
Thank you.

134
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,549
Pinagpala Special Torta.

135
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:56,554
Hello, ma’am. Good day to you.

136
00:09:57,638 --> 00:10:02,059
We’d like to request a delivery
and also order some torta.

137
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:04,437
Sure, sir and ma’am.

138
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,276
What would you like to order?

139
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,069
It’s true, bro.

140
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:17,158
I really am embarrassing.

141
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:19,327
Imagine that…

142
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,872
I was supposed to study here,

143
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,626
but instead…

144
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:30,171
I got caught in a drug buy-bust.

145
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:32,089
What was that?

146
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:38,763
It’s so embarrassing for Mom and Dad.

147
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:44,143
But most of all for you, bro.

148
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:51,442
You were the one
who sacrificed so much for me.

149
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,741
What happened to you was not your fault.

150
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,459
You were just in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

151
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:12,296
I’m the one you should blame.

152
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:16,509
Because that wouldn’t have happened
if I had been there for you.

153
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:22,390
Come here. Stop being dramatic.

154
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:23,432
Come on.

155
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,003
I will avenge you, bro.

156
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:58,134
I’ll go after whoever did this to you.

157
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:17,611
There you go, Betchay.
This is very simple.

158
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,239
Go to the market now

159
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:22,450
because I already called Aling Pacing.

160
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,119
I ordered extra ingredients.

161
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:27,705
I ordered vanilla, eggs,

162
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:29,540
basically everything on this list.

163
00:12:29,623 --> 00:12:30,958
Here! It’s very easy.

164
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:32,084
-Go now, hurry!
-Yes, ma'am!

165
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,127
I’ll take care of it.

166
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:35,296
It’s important. I need it right away.

167
00:12:36,505 --> 00:12:37,339
Angel!

168
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,383
-You need to cook all of that now.
-Yes.

169
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:43,846
What are the extra ingredients for?

170
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:44,805
Honey,

171
00:12:45,389 --> 00:12:48,601
someone ordered a huge amount of torta.

172
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:51,061
Of course, our ingredients aren’t enough,

173
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:53,105
since we only stock a small amount.

174
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:54,607
So I bought extra.

175
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:56,233
And where are they from?

176
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:59,987
Right! They’re from Manila!

177
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:03,282
-From Manila?
-Yes!

178
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:05,159
So someone already knows about our bakery?

179
00:13:05,242 --> 00:13:06,410
Yes!

180
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:09,580
But they said they’re friends with Mikoy!

181
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:13,542
And Mikoy apparently told them
about our torta recipe.

182
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,586
So, yes! They ordered a lot.

183
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,087
I wonder who that is?

184
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,422
Oh no.

185
00:13:18,506 --> 00:13:20,591
They said they’re really
friends with Mikoy.

186
00:13:20,674 --> 00:13:24,678
And they even asked where Mikoy is now.

187
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:27,389
I told them he’s back from Prague

188
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:30,351
and now in Manila
and already has a new job.

189
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,355
I wonder who it is.

190
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:45,699
Where do you think you're going?

191
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:53,832
What are you doing here?

192
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:58,212
I should be asking you that.

193
00:13:58,295 --> 00:14:00,172
What are you doing here?

194
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:04,260
That you’re already here in Manila.

195
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:06,178
If we hadn’t called your mother,

196
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:07,805
we wouldn’t have known where you are

197
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,139
or what happened to you.

198
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:10,808
Why did you call my mother?

199
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:15,396
I had no choice. I needed to talk to you.

200
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:16,855
Because there’s a threat against you now!

201
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,786
Yes! Yes!

202
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:32,872
Is there a problem?

203
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:35,040
Nothing.

204
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:36,166
I was looking for you.

205
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:42,089
Angelito’s university is really beautiful.

206
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:44,466
Yes.

207
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,221
No.

208
00:14:58,188 --> 00:15:00,399
Ah, it’s her. She…

209
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:04,778
And I think you found
what you were looking for.

210
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:07,656
Yes!

211
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,701
Right! I was just asking around

212
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,871
because Angelito’s university is so big.

213
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:15,289
I couldn’t see you.

214
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,293
I’ll be late for my class.

215
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:22,421
Yes!

216
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:24,381
Thank you, ma’am!

217
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:33,223
Of course. Definitely. Where are we going?

218
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:36,852
-Let’s go!
-Come on!

219
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:44,568
Oh, how are you?

220
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:46,153
Chiara is there!

221
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,573
So, what happened? Did Chiara see you?

222
00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:52,242
Yes! I was careless! Let’s go!

223
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:54,495
What the… Alex!

224
00:15:54,578 --> 00:15:56,664
You know that’s dangerous!

225
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,624
She must not recognize you!

226
00:15:58,707 --> 00:16:01,543
Why do you think we need
to be careful around Chiara?

227
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:04,046
Do you think she knows
what her parents are doing?

228
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,255
I don’t know,

229
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:06,465
but one thing I’m sure of,

230
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,842
we cannot trust her either. Okay?

231
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,594
And under no circumstances

232
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:13,013
should she recognize or see us.

233
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:14,890
Okay?

234
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:32,783
and she told me about
your worries at work.

235
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,493
About your being COO.

236
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,621
Well, that’s a valid concern.

237
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:40,916
Because this is new for Mikoy. Right?

238
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:45,629
Yes. There’s quite
a difference in managing,

239
00:16:45,713 --> 00:16:48,048
running a bakery,

240
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:50,467
versus managing a big company.

241
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:54,471
Sweetheart, you don’t need to worry.

242
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:58,976
And if you have any problem,
you can always turn to me.

243
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:03,856
May I just ask something?

244
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:07,401
Why not let Chiara
run the company instead?

245
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:09,486
She’s capable.

246
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,823
Actually, this is a very good question.

247
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:15,534
Yes, indeed. Child, why didn’t you…

248
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,120
answer?

249
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:20,539
I just thought about it.

250
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:23,042
Of course, you’re super educated.

251
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:27,755
You graduated from a very prestigious
and very expensive school.

252
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:31,842
Of course, you also know
your daddy’s business.

253
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:34,678
For me, she’s really
the perfect one for this.

254
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:47,066
Why not?

255
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:50,694
Simple. I don’t want to.

256
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:53,781
I don’t want to do it. Period.

257
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,701
What do you want to do?

258
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:22,643
Excuse me.

259
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:55,217
Are you okay?

260
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:06,145
I don’t think that question
should have been asked.

261
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:09,148
But it is a good question.

262
00:19:09,231 --> 00:19:10,482
No!

263
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,068
I should have thought of that.

264
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:16,697
By the way, that’s why you're mad
at your mommy and daddy.

265
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:21,201
You’re being forced
to take over their business.

266
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:25,622
Chiara, sorry.

267
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:28,417
I was really insensitive there.

268
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:33,046
It’s okay.

269
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:36,967
At least now

270
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:40,137
you know the life I’ve been living.

271
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:45,350
They say, the more you know someone,

272
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,061
the more you love them.

273
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:56,195
Isn’t it, the more you know,

274
00:19:57,154 --> 00:19:58,113
the more you hate?

275
00:19:58,739 --> 00:19:59,615
Really?

276
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,409
-No take-backs?
-Just kidding!

277
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,120
This one is no joke though.

278
00:20:09,082 --> 00:20:10,834
Don’t worry.

279
00:20:11,668 --> 00:20:12,878
I’m here.

280
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,757
If you don’t want to take over
their business yet,

281
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,343
then I will go first.

282
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:22,721
So you won’t be pressured
by your mommy and daddy.

283
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:25,807
Okay?

284
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:39,154
For coming into my life.

285
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:49,581
Believe it or not,

286
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:56,255
I just want a simple and normal life.

287
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:03,136
So, sorry,

288
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:06,640
because now you’re the one
in a complicated situation.

289
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,395
But I will be forever grateful

290
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:14,648
for your help to me and my family.

291
00:22:07,951 --> 00:22:08,827
Okay.

292
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:24,176
Because starting today,

293
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:28,263
you will be handling very delicate
and sensitive information.

294
00:22:28,346 --> 00:22:30,432
So, nothing must leak

295
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:34,061
from any information inside this agency.

296
00:22:34,144 --> 00:22:35,187
Okay?

297
00:22:57,959 --> 00:23:01,046
Here, we will see the clue
that we are all looking for.

298
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:19,147
Special Agent Sianong,

299
00:23:19,231 --> 00:23:23,318
give me one good reason
why I should not suspend you without pay

300
00:23:23,401 --> 00:23:25,570
and send you to Timbuktu!

301
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:28,490
Sorry. Sorry. Sorry, Sir.

302
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:31,743
I wanted a proper welcome
for our team members.

303
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:33,245
Sorry. Okay.

304
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:44,589
But unlike that video,

305
00:23:45,632 --> 00:23:47,259
we don’t need to be afraid anymore.

306
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:53,932
Looks like we finally have a chance.

307
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:04,985
And here he is now.

308
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:11,533
You know, he could become a celebrity.

309
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:14,828
Looks like he’s really going to shine.

310
00:24:25,046 --> 00:24:28,717
Is he going to be launched
as a new loveteam on primetime TV?

311
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:39,561
Not a loveteam.

312
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:41,396
But he is not slated for primetime.

313
00:24:42,063 --> 00:24:44,441
Because he is now the new
Chief Operations Officer

314
00:24:44,524 --> 00:24:46,443
of Vertex Global Holdings!

315
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,029
The company of the Valtrovis!

316
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:54,618
VERTEX GLOBAL

317
00:25:02,250 --> 00:25:05,253
The past week, he was introduced
to the entire company,

318
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:08,840
and he was briefed
about company operations.

319
00:25:10,675 --> 00:25:13,136
Here, Viktor Valtrovi taught him

320
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:15,680
the core business of Vertex,

321
00:25:15,764 --> 00:25:19,809
and that is repackaging Filipino products

322
00:25:19,893 --> 00:25:22,938
and exporting them
to various markets in Europe.

323
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:28,235
We have reason to believe
that Viktor is using this

324
00:25:28,318 --> 00:25:32,364
to export illegal shipments to Europe.

325
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:45,043
But how does he do it?

326
00:25:45,126 --> 00:25:49,714
How does he smuggle his illegal shipments?

327
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:57,555
Can our asset answer these questions?

328
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:52,444
If you're really struggling,
you can walk away from this mission.

329
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,529
You're saying it's okay with you

330
00:26:54,612 --> 00:26:57,741
if I don't continue spying on them?
Against the Moravianos?

331
00:26:59,034 --> 00:27:02,162
I heard that you want to kill Mikoy.

332
00:27:04,164 --> 00:27:07,375
The one who ordered is your friend.

333
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:09,836
The name is Alex.

334
00:27:09,919 --> 00:27:12,088
Who's that friend of yours, sweetheart?

335
00:27:16,384 --> 00:27:17,844
How did you guys meet?
